# EnvSpec

##### `.envspec`
``` sh
# Basic stuff
APP_NAME=EnvSpec
NOT_A_SECRET="I don't care if this gets leaked"

# Secret stuff
ENVIRONMENT=
SECRET_API_KEY=
```

##### ⬇️
##### `.env`
``` sh
# Basic Stuff
APP_NAME=EnvSpec
NOT_A_SECRET="I don't care if this gets leaked"

# Secret stuff
ENVIRONMENT=
SECRET_API_KEY=
```

### What It Does

- Specify which environment variables your application requires
- Capture those variables from your CI pipeline configuration
- Generate a deployable, environment-specific dotenv file.

### Basic AF

- No new syntax
  - You already know how it works
  - Comments and breaks will be preserved
- It's a single bash script
  - Commit it to your repo
  - Runs anywhere
  - No installer
  - No external dependancies

### Convenience of a dotenv, security of a CI workflow

- Non-secret, environment-independant values can still be stored in the file
- Secret or enviroment-specific variables still go in the CI configuration
- Will emit helpful error messages into the pipeline logs if expected values are not provided
